WEBVTT

00:05.172 --> 00:05.939 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
GWEN IFILL: Good evening.

00:05.939 --> 00:07.474 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
I'm Gwen Ifill.

00:07.474 --> 00:09.576 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
JUDY WOODRUFF: And
I'm Judy Woodruff.

00:09.576 --> 00:14.514 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
On the "NewsHour" tonight:
Hillary Clinton takes a break
from campaigning after a
pneumonia

00:14.514 --> 00:20.320 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
diagnosis -- why both
candidates' health is playing a
major role this presidential
election.

00:20.320 --> 00:24.758 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
GWEN IFILL: I travel to Colorado
to talk to voters in the most
Republican area of the

00:24.758 --> 00:26.493 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
state.

00:26.493 --> 00:30.097 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
MAN: Well, the choices
are dismal, I think.

00:30.097 --> 00:37.204 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
It's just kind of a weird time,
a weird election, sort of sad in
a sense, I guess.

00:37.204 --> 00:42.075 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Plus: deep
corruption in the world's
youngest nation.

00:42.075 --> 00:46.179 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
A report reveals South Sudan's
leaders profiting from the
country's strife.

00:46.179 --> 00:49.383 align:left position:25%,start line:86.67% size:75%
GWEN IFILL: And
Rethinking College.

00:49.383 --> 00:54.488 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
The first installment of our new
series looks at the first urban
work college in the country.

00:54.488 --> 00:57.557 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
It's remaking its mission with
a football-field-turned-farm.

00:57.557 --> 01:01.461 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
MICHAEL SORRELL, President, Paul
Quinn College: Our students are
getting two forms of education.

01:01.461 --> 01:05.499 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
They're getting a rigorous
liberal arts training, and
they're also getting real world
work experience.

01:05.499 --> 01:11.638 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: All that and more
on tonight's "PBS NewsHour."

01:11.638 --> 01:15.509 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
(BREAK)

01:15.509 --> 01:26.386 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: The questions are
swirling in the presidential
campaign this evening:

01:26.386 --> 01:30.657 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
How much do voters know about
the candidates' health, and how
much should they know?

01:30.657 --> 01:34.328 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
The issue leaped to the
fore in the last 24 hours.

01:34.328 --> 01:38.065 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
WOMAN: She was diagnosed
with pneumonia on Friday.

01:38.065 --> 01:43.470 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: The cable news
banners told the story, Hillary
Clinton's health front

01:43.470 --> 01:48.375 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
and center, after she appeared
to stumble when she abruptly
left Sunday's 9/11 ceremony

01:48.375 --> 01:51.511 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
in New York City.

01:51.511 --> 01:55.849 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Hours later, her doctor said the
68-year-old Democratic nominee
had been diagnosed with

01:55.849 --> 01:59.453 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
pneumonia last Friday.

01:59.453 --> 02:04.691 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
The Clinton campaign pledged
today that more information on
her health is forthcoming.

02:04.691 --> 02:06.927 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
BRIAN FALLON, Clinton Campaign
Spokesman: We're going to be
releasing that to further

02:06.927 --> 02:10.330 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
put to rest any lingering
concerns about what you saw
yesterday.

02:10.330 --> 02:14.701 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
It really is the case that there
is no other undisclosed
condition.

02:14.701 --> 02:19.206 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Clinton scrapped
a California trip, and instead
planned to phone in to a

02:19.206 --> 02:22.909 align:left position:25%,start line:86.67% size:75%
San Francisco
fund-raiser tonight.

02:22.909 --> 02:27.981 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And late today, she tweeted:
"I'm feeling fine and getting
better."

02:27.981 --> 02:30.851 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
That left running mate Tim Kaine
to take up the issue in Dayton,
Ohio.

02:30.851 --> 02:33.587 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
SEN.

02:33.587 --> 02:34.554 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
TIM KAINE (D-VA), Vice
Presidential Candidate: I have
just been on the campaign since
July

02:34.554 --> 02:36.957 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
22.

02:36.957 --> 02:39.192 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Hillary Clinton has been on
the trail for 18 months.

02:39.192 --> 02:42.462 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
Her energy staggers me.

02:42.462 --> 02:44.197 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
I have a hard time
keeping up with her.

02:44.197 --> 02:46.500 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
(CHEERING AND APPLAUSE)

02:46.500 --> 02:49.636 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Meanwhile,
Republican Donald Trump was
restrained in his reaction.

02:49.636 --> 02:51.004 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
DONALD TRUMP (R), Presidential
Candidate: But I just hope that
she gets well, and gets

02:51.004 --> 02:53.507 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
back on the trail.

02:53.507 --> 02:57.310 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Trump has
released little about his own
health, but promised today he
will

02:57.310 --> 02:59.579 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
be putting out more
information as well.

02:59.579 --> 03:02.049 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
DONALD TRUMP: This last
week, I took a physical.

03:02.049 --> 03:05.519 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
And I will be releasing
when the numbers come in.

03:05.519 --> 03:08.588 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
Hopefully, they're
going to be good.

03:08.588 --> 03:09.489 align:left position:25%,start line:86.67% size:75%
I think they're
going to be good.

03:09.489 --> 03:11.758 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
I feel great.

03:11.758 --> 03:15.962 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
But when the numbers come in, I
will be releasing very, very
specific numbers.

03:15.962 --> 03:20.333 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Trump's main
focus today was a different
issue: Clinton's Friday night

03:20.333 --> 03:23.070 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
comments about his supporters.

03:23.070 --> 03:27.107 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
It's fodder for a new
Trump campaign ad.

03:27.107 --> 03:30.077 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
HILLARY RODHAM CLINTON (D),
Presidential Candidate: You
could put half of Trump's
supporters into

03:30.077 --> 03:36.316 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
what I call the basket of
deplorables, the racist, sexist,
homophobic, xenophobic,
Islamophobic,

03:36.316 --> 03:38.118 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
you name it.

03:38.118 --> 03:41.588 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
NARRATOR: People like you,
you, and you, deplorable.

03:41.588 --> 03:46.093 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: And it was fodder
for Trump himself on the
campaign trail today during

03:46.093 --> 03:48.495 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
a speech in Baltimore.

03:48.495 --> 03:53.567 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
DONALD TRUMP: We have the
support of cops, and soldiers,
carpenters and welders, the

03:53.567 --> 03:58.405 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
young and the old, and millions
of working-class families.

03:58.405 --> 04:01.241 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
These were among the countless
Americans that Hillary Clinton
called deplorable, irredeemable,

04:01.241 --> 04:03.743 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
and un-American.

04:03.743 --> 04:10.083 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Trump's next
stop, one of the battleground
states, North Carolina, this

04:10.083 --> 04:13.353 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
evening.

04:13.353 --> 04:17.791 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
We will examine the issue of
presidential candidates' health
more fully after the news

04:17.791 --> 04:20.627 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
summary.

04:20.627 --> 04:24.464 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
GWEN IFILL: In the day's other
news: a cease-fire in Syria
negotiated by the U.S. and
Russia

04:24.464 --> 04:27.667 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
is now officially in force.

04:27.667 --> 04:32.639 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
It took effect at sunset,
although government attacks
continued in the city of Aleppo.

04:32.639 --> 04:36.943 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Meanwhile, Syrian President
Bashar al-Assad appeared in a
recaptured Damascus suburb,

04:36.943 --> 04:41.248 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
and insisted he means to control
the whole country again.

04:41.248 --> 04:44.751 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
BASHAR AL-ASSAD, President of
Syria (through translator): The
Syrian state is determined

04:44.751 --> 04:50.090 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
to recover every area from the
terrorists, to restore safety
and security, to rebuild,

04:50.090 --> 04:53.894 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
to rebuild the infrastructure,
to rebuild whatever is destroyed
by all means.

04:53.894 --> 04:57.364 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
We call upon all Syrians to
move towards reconciliation.

04:57.364 --> 05:01.268 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
GWEN IFILL: A number of rebel
groups expressed misgivings
about the agreement, including

05:01.268 --> 05:03.737 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
over how it would be enforced.

05:03.737 --> 05:07.841 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Later, Secretary of State
John Kerry defended the deal.

05:07.841 --> 05:11.144 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
He even talked of approving
Syrian strikes against al-Qaida
militants once known as the

05:11.144 --> 05:13.780 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
al-Nusra Front.

05:13.780 --> 05:18.685 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JOHN KERRY, U.S. Secretary of
State: Assad is not supposed to
be bombing the opposition

05:18.685 --> 05:21.688 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
because there is a cease-fire.

05:21.688 --> 05:26.526 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Now, he is allowed and will be
to target Nusra, but that would
be on strikes that are agreed

05:26.526 --> 05:29.529 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
upon with Russia and
the United States.

05:29.529 --> 05:32.599 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
GWEN IFILL: That would mark the
first U.S. cooperation with the
Assad government since

05:32.599 --> 05:35.702 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
the Syrian civil war began.

05:35.702 --> 05:39.472 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
Within hours, the State
Department walked it back,
saying there is no such
provision

05:39.472 --> 05:42.008 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
in the agreement.

05:42.008 --> 05:46.746 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: China today
rejected U.S. calls that it do
more to stop North Korea's
nuclear

05:46.746 --> 05:48.748 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
program.

05:48.748 --> 05:53.086 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
It came days after the North
conducted a fifth nuclear test.

05:53.086 --> 05:57.023 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
In Beijing, the foreign ministry
said Washington stoked the
tensions, and should bear the
brunt

05:57.023 --> 05:59.559 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
of dealing with it.

05:59.559 --> 06:02.295 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
HUA CHUNYING, Spokeswoman,
Chinese Ministry of Foreign
Affairs (through translator):
The

06:02.295 --> 06:06.333 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
nub of the North Korean nuclear
issue is not in China, but in
the United States.

06:06.333 --> 06:09.502 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
The U.S. should earnestly work
on a tangible and effective
solution.

06:09.502 --> 06:13.073 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
There is an old saying in China:
Whoever started the trouble
should end it.

06:13.073 --> 06:16.676 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Thus, the U.S. should take
on its due responsibility.

06:16.676 --> 06:20.313 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: The Chinese
spokeswoman also voiced doubts
about U.S. calls for new
sanctions

06:20.313 --> 06:22.749 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
against the North.

06:22.749 --> 06:26.186 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Meanwhile, South Korea warned
that the North is ready to set
off another nuclear blast

06:26.186 --> 06:29.055 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
at any time.

06:29.055 --> 06:34.794 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
GWEN IFILL: North Korea is
reeling from disastrous flooding
after a typhoon hit late last
month.

06:34.794 --> 06:40.600 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
A U.N. report says the storm
killed at least 130 people and
destroyed thousands of homes.

06:40.600 --> 06:44.337 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
North Korean state TV today
showed footage of recovery
efforts.

06:44.337 --> 06:48.008 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Workers cleared debris and
worked to repair railway lines.

06:48.008 --> 06:52.946 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
JUDY WOODRUFF: In the
Philippines, outspoken President
Rodrigo Duterte is now demanding

06:52.946 --> 06:57.817 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
the U.S. withdraw all troops
from his country's south.

06:57.817 --> 07:03.056 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
The U.S. has advisers there
working with Philippine troops
against pro-al-Qaida fighters.

07:03.056 --> 07:08.695 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Today, in Manila, Duterte blamed
the American presence for
inflaming Islamist groups.

07:08.695 --> 07:10.997 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
RODRIGO DUTERTE, Philippine
President (through translator):
There are a lot of Americans,

07:10.997 --> 07:14.734 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
white people there,
and they have to go.

07:14.734 --> 07:17.270 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
The conflict there will only get
worse if they see American
soldiers, and there will

07:17.270 --> 07:19.639 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
be more bloodshed.

07:19.639 --> 07:24.044 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Duterte said the
bad blood goes back to U.S.
efforts to stamp out Muslim

07:24.044 --> 07:29.282 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
rebellions in the early 1900's,
when the Philippines was a U.S.
colony.

07:29.282 --> 07:34.187 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
GWEN IFILL: Back in this
country, newly discovered
documents show the sugar
industry began funding

07:34.187 --> 07:39.292 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
research decades ago to dismiss
links between sugar and heart
disease.

07:39.292 --> 07:43.863 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The journal "JAMA Internal
Medicine" today published an
analysis of correspondence
between

07:43.863 --> 07:47.100 align:left position:25%,start line:86.67% size:75%
the industry and
Harvard researchers.

07:47.100 --> 07:50.904 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
It said the resulting studies
successfully cast doubt about
the hazards of sucrose, while

07:50.904 --> 07:53.940 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
promoting fat as the culprit.

07:53.940 --> 07:59.045 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: And soccer
injuries are soaring among
American children.

07:59.045 --> 08:03.149 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
A study in the journal
"Pediatrics" finds the number
treated in emergency rooms
jumped

08:03.149 --> 08:07.287 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
78 percent between
1990 and 2014.

08:07.287 --> 08:11.124 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
It was fueled, in
part, by concussions.

08:11.124 --> 08:15.395 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Researchers at the Nationwide
Children's Hospital in Columbus,
Ohio, say that it's also due

08:15.395 --> 08:18.264 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
to soccer's growing popularity.

08:18.264 --> 08:22.602 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
GWEN IFILL: Wall Street
recovered some today from
Friday's big losses.

08:22.602 --> 08:27.841 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
The Dow Jones industrial average
gained 239 points to close at
18325.

08:27.841 --> 08:34.013 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
The Nasdaq rose nearly 86 points
and the S&amp;P 500 added 31.

08:34.013 --> 08:38.084 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Still to come on
the "NewsHour": the debate over
the public's right to know

08:38.084 --> 08:44.424 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
about presidential nominees'
health; lifelong Republicans
rethinking their loyalty in the

08:44.424 --> 08:49.229 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
traditionally swing state of
Colorado; calling out South
Sudanese leaders for getting
rich

08:49.229 --> 09:03.977 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
off the country's
troubles; and much more.

09:03.977 --> 09:08.948 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Now a closer look at just how
much the public has a right to
know about the health of the

09:08.948 --> 09:13.920 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
American president or a
presidential candidate, and what
earlier presidents have and have

09:13.920 --> 09:17.290 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
not disclosed about their
personal health histories.

09:17.290 --> 09:20.760 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
For that, we turn to
Dr. Howard Markel.

09:20.760 --> 09:24.798 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
He's director of the Center for
the History of Medicine at the
University of Michigan.

09:24.798 --> 09:27.734 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
He's also author of a number of
books on health and infectious
diseases.

09:27.734 --> 09:31.471 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
Dr. Markel, welcome.

09:31.471 --> 09:34.841 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Hillary Clinton's campaign says
that her pneumonia is not
severe.

09:34.841 --> 09:37.110 align:left position:25%,start line:86.67% size:75%
Just how serious
can pneumonia be?

09:37.110 --> 09:39.746 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
DR.

09:39.746 --> 09:39.512 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
HOWARD MARKEL, Director, Center
for the History of Medicine,
University of Michigan: Well,

09:39.512 --> 09:40.880 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
pneumonia can be quite serious.

09:40.880 --> 09:43.316 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
People can die of it.

09:43.316 --> 09:47.554 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
They used to call it the old
man's friend in the years before
antibiotics.

09:47.554 --> 09:52.425 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
But now with taking antibiotics,
taking care of yourself and
resting, it is quite an easy

09:52.425 --> 09:55.228 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
thing to treat.

09:55.228 --> 10:00.800 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: We saw -- I guess
it was just reported this
afternoon on Politico that
Hillary

10:00.800 --> 10:05.538 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Clinton's staff is saying she
doesn't prefer to drink water
often.

10:05.538 --> 10:07.373 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Could that have contributed
to what happened yesterday?

10:07.373 --> 10:08.741 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
DR.

10:08.741 --> 10:09.509 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
HOWARD MARKEL: Absolutely.

10:09.509 --> 10:11.945 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
Think about it.

10:11.945 --> 10:15.315 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
You're tired, you're sick,
you're out in the sun, which
dehydrates us all, whether we're

10:15.315 --> 10:18.218 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
aware of it or not.

10:18.218 --> 10:22.021 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And that could very well have
been what caused that wobbly
step that everyone has seen and

10:22.021 --> 10:24.591 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
talked about today.

10:24.591 --> 10:29.162 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Well, let me ask
you, both of these campaigns,
both Trump and Clinton

10:29.162 --> 10:34.234 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
are now saying, in the next few
days, they are going to be
releasing fuller medical
histories,

10:34.234 --> 10:38.071 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
we're going to know more
about their medical story.

10:38.071 --> 10:42.242 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
What do the American voters
have a right to know?

10:42.242 --> 10:45.178 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
What should people know in order
to know whether these two
individuals are healthy or not?

10:45.178 --> 10:47.046 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
DR.

10:47.046 --> 10:48.948 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
HOWARD MARKEL: Well, I
think it's very important.

10:48.948 --> 10:52.852 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And I think American voters do
have the right to know about the
health of the people who

10:52.852 --> 10:58.157 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
are running for the most
powerful job in the world.

10:58.157 --> 11:03.663 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
It is very easy to present one's
health history, and yet it's
become very tangled and diffuse,

11:03.663 --> 11:06.466 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
just like people's tax returns.

11:06.466 --> 11:11.437 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
But I think both these pieces of
information are valid for people
to ask about.

11:11.437 --> 11:17.410 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: And so what are
some aspects of their health
that you think should be
disclosed

11:17.410 --> 11:18.678 align:left position:25%,start line:86.67% size:75%
when they do put
these histories out?

11:18.678 --> 11:21.281 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
DR.

11:21.281 --> 11:25.451 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
HOWARD MARKEL: Well, I think
just the basic top-to-bottom
physical examination, mental

11:25.451 --> 11:31.357 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
health examination, a recording
of the medications they may or
may not take, past illnesses,

11:31.357 --> 11:35.161 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
illnesses that may run in their
family, a general medical
history.

11:35.161 --> 11:40.300 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Now, remember, this hasn't
really been done all that much
since 1992.

11:40.300 --> 11:45.905 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And it was Paul Tsongas who
didn't tell the American people
precisely about his
non-Hodgkin's

11:45.905 --> 11:47.106 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
lymphoma.

11:47.106 --> 11:47.907 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
He said he was cured.

11:47.907 --> 11:50.376 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
He wasn't.

11:50.376 --> 11:55.148 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Had he won the rest of the
campaign and run for president,
he probably would have been

11:55.148 --> 11:57.183 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
quite ill during his presidency.

11:57.183 --> 12:00.753 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
So these things do matter.

12:00.753 --> 12:04.891 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And I think it's one more piece
of information that we as voters
have a right to know about.

12:04.891 --> 12:07.260 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: And, of course,
there are other examples as
well.

12:07.260 --> 12:08.361 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
People think of John F.
Kennedy, Addison's disease.

12:08.361 --> 12:09.762 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
DR.

12:09.762 --> 12:11.230 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
HOWARD MARKEL: That's right.

12:11.230 --> 12:11.364 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: And a number
of other presidents.

12:11.364 --> 12:12.632 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
DR.

12:12.632 --> 12:15.001 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
HOWARD MARKEL: Yes.

12:15.001 --> 12:20.006 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And really back to Kennedy, or
Roosevelt or even Woodrow
Wilson's health, these were an

12:20.006 --> 12:25.211 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
era where medicine could not do
all that much for these serious
diseases.

12:25.211 --> 12:30.249 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Today, more and more people are
living full and healthy lives
with chronic illnesses.

12:30.249 --> 12:35.088 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And I have got to tell you,
having turned 50 myself quite a
few years ago, the warranty

12:35.088 --> 12:39.592 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
on your body runs out at that
point, and we all have problems
with our bodies.

12:39.592 --> 12:43.830 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
And so Mrs. Clinton's pneumonia
is community-acquired.

12:43.830 --> 12:48.935 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
It's a very normal thing to do
to contract, particularly when
you're shaking hands, and

12:48.935 --> 12:54.407 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
working a grueling campaign, and
flying on airplanes and stuff.

12:54.407 --> 12:58.878 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And I have to tell you that most
doctors would give the advice,
why don't you take a break

12:58.878 --> 13:03.416 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
from this grueling campaign for
a day or so and rest, like any
human being whose body

13:03.416 --> 13:05.018 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
gets sick?

13:05.018 --> 13:05.852 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Well,
you mentioned age.

13:05.852 --> 13:07.520 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
Hillary Clinton is 68.

13:07.520 --> 13:11.290 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
Donald Trump is 70.

13:11.290 --> 13:16.262 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
How much is age a factor in
this, as you describe, grueling
job they both want to take on?

13:16.262 --> 13:18.331 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
DR.

13:18.331 --> 13:21.801 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
HOWARD MARKEL: Well, it's hard
to say with each 70-year-old.

13:21.801 --> 13:27.273 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
One 70-year-old may be quite
fatigued by this type of a
schedule.

13:27.273 --> 13:30.476 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Other people -- and it seems Mr.
Trump and Mrs. Clinton are those
types -- are energized

13:30.476 --> 13:32.645 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
by it.

13:32.645 --> 13:36.182 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
So, it really is a case-by-case
person -- case-by-case
situation.

13:36.182 --> 13:40.920 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
But, you know, most people over
65 should get a pneumonia shot
and also should get a

13:40.920 --> 13:42.155 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
flu shot every year.

13:42.155 --> 13:43.489 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
So that's something you can do.

13:43.489 --> 13:45.091 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
But it's hard to say.

13:45.091 --> 13:47.360 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
These sounds like extremely
energetic people.

13:47.360 --> 13:50.063 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
They sound like very
healthy people.

13:50.063 --> 13:53.366 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
I'm a little puzzled why they
just don't tell us what's going
on.

13:53.366 --> 13:58.271 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Well, again, as
we prepare to see whatever these
campaigns release, how

13:58.271 --> 13:59.972 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
will we know we're
getting the full story?

13:59.972 --> 14:01.908 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
DR.

14:01.908 --> 14:05.211 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
HOWARD MARKEL: That is
difficult, and we don't know.

14:05.211 --> 14:11.150 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And particularly the briefer the
report is, there may be stuff
that you're not seeing,

14:11.150 --> 14:17.523 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
or you could get a data dump,
like John McCain did a few years
back where he released thousands

14:17.523 --> 14:22.462 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
of pages of his medical history
and gave journalists only about
three or four hours to review
them.

14:22.462 --> 14:25.465 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
I'm a medical professor, and I
couldn't do it in that time.

14:25.465 --> 14:29.902 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
So there's different ways that
people can be somewhat shifty or
less than transparent

14:29.902 --> 14:32.405 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
with their health data.

14:32.405 --> 14:39.112 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
I think it's high time in this
modern era of great medicine and
great health prevention

14:39.112 --> 14:43.149 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
that our presidential candidates
just tell us what is going on in
their bodies.

14:43.149 --> 14:45.818 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
And we can make those decisions
one way or the other.

14:45.818 --> 14:48.454 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Well, we will be
looking for what each campaign
has to say in the coming

14:48.454 --> 14:49.822 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
days.

14:49.822 --> 14:50.423 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
Dr. Howard Markel, we thank you.

14:50.423 --> 14:51.791 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
DR.

14:51.791 --> 14:54.160 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
HOWARD MARKEL: Thank you.

14:54.160 --> 14:58.331 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: And on our Web
site, you can find a guide to
pneumonia, what causes it

14:58.331 --> 15:00.767 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
and what makes it a potentially
dangerous illness.

15:00.767 --> 15:04.337 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
That's at PBS.org/NewsHour.

15:04.337 --> 15:09.575 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
GWEN IFILL: For more on how
health issues are dogging
Hillary Clinton and raising
questions

15:09.575 --> 15:13.679 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
of transparency for both
candidates, it's time for
Politics Monday with Tamara
Keith

15:13.679 --> 15:18.551 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
of NPR and Susan Page,
Washington bureau chief for USA
Today.

15:18.551 --> 15:22.421 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Tam, we just heard Dr. Markel
say the warranty begins to run
out after 50, and he doesn't

15:22.421 --> 15:25.424 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
understand why people just don't
tell us what their issues are.

15:25.424 --> 15:28.494 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
How did health become
central to this campaign?

15:28.494 --> 15:32.732 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
TAMARA KEITH, National Public
Radio: Well, Hillary Clinton did
have a coughing fit about

15:32.732 --> 15:37.303 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
a week ago on the campaign trail
that interrupted a press
conference and also later --
earlier

15:37.303 --> 15:42.241 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
interrupted a rally
where she was speaking.

15:42.241 --> 15:48.381 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
That was -- there was already a
lot circulating about her health
that was completely
unsubstantiated,

15:48.381 --> 15:55.388 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
a lot of rumors, conspiracy
theories, and Donald Trump
talking about her stamina.

15:55.388 --> 16:00.893 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
So this was floating in the
ether, when, yesterday, at the
9/11 commemoration, she faltered
as

16:00.893 --> 16:03.095 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
she was leaving.

16:03.095 --> 16:06.032 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Her knees buckled and she had
trouble getting into her van.

16:06.032 --> 16:08.601 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
She took off in that van.

16:08.601 --> 16:11.437 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
And the press wasn't
allowed to follow.

16:11.437 --> 16:15.741 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And about 90 minutes later, the
campaign said, well, she's at
Chelsea Clinton's house.

16:15.741 --> 16:18.678 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
She's feeling better,
and she was overheated.

16:18.678 --> 16:21.047 align:left position:25%,start line:86.67% size:75%
GWEN IFILL: Then
hours later said...

16:21.047 --> 16:22.815 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
TAMARA KEITH: Then
hours later...

16:22.815 --> 16:24.350 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
GWEN IFILL: Well, it seemed like
a long time if you were covering
it, I'm sure.

16:24.350 --> 16:24.617 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
For those of who weren't
paying as close attention...

16:24.617 --> 16:26.252 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
(CROSSTALK)

16:26.252 --> 16:27.186 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
TAMARA KEITH: Well, it
was about 5:00 p.m.

16:27.186 --> 16:28.254 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
GWEN IFILL: It was
the end of the day.

16:28.254 --> 16:28.721 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
TAMARA KEITH: It was
the end of the day...

16:28.721 --> 16:31.290 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
GWEN IFILL: Right.

16:31.290 --> 16:35.061 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
TAMARA KEITH: ... when the
doctor, her doctor, released a
statement saying she was
overheated,

16:35.061 --> 16:40.533 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
dehydrated, and, oh, by the way,
on Friday, three days earlier,
was diagnosed with pneumonia,

16:40.533 --> 16:42.335 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
and they hadn't told
anyone about that before.

16:42.335 --> 16:45.037 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
GWEN IFILL: Well, that's
the point, Susan.

16:45.037 --> 16:49.108 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Was this really about -- is our
concern really about her health
or is it about the fact of

16:49.108 --> 16:52.144 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
the failure to disclose
in a timely fashion?

16:52.144 --> 16:53.546 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
SUSAN PAGE, Washington Bureau
Chief, USA Today: I think both
things are issues.

16:53.546 --> 16:55.982 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
I think she will now need to
come out and show that she's
healthy and vigorous and has

16:55.982 --> 16:58.484 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
stamina.

16:58.484 --> 17:01.487 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
She has -- the fact that she was
diagnosed with pneumonia, and we
didn't know about it,

17:01.487 --> 17:07.660 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
and had this incident caught on
a video has legitimized some of
the critiques that Trump

17:07.660 --> 17:10.196 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
and Rudy Giuliani in particular
have been making that she's --
that there's some question

17:10.196 --> 17:11.097 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
about her health.

17:11.097 --> 17:12.932 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
(CROSSTALK)

17:12.932 --> 17:13.566 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
GWEN IFILL: Donald Trump,
who has not released his...

17:13.566 --> 17:14.133 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
SUSAN PAGE: His own
health records.

17:14.133 --> 17:15.701 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
That's right.

17:15.701 --> 17:16.369 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
GWEN IFILL: OK, just
to make that point.

17:16.369 --> 17:17.970 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
SUSAN PAGE: Yes, absolutely.

17:17.970 --> 17:20.106 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
But I think her failure to
disclose it is also an issue.

17:20.106 --> 17:23.542 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And it goes to a different
vulnerability she has, which is,
is she straightforward with

17:23.542 --> 17:25.945 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
the Americans whose
votes she wants to get?

17:25.945 --> 17:27.613 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
GWEN IFILL: And they say there
is a higher standard for the
woman candidate.

17:27.613 --> 17:28.714 align:left position:25%,start line:86.67% size:75%
That's what the
Clinton people say.

17:28.714 --> 17:29.482 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
TAMARA KEITH: Yes.

17:29.482 --> 17:30.716 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
They do.

17:30.716 --> 17:32.518 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
They do say that.

17:32.518 --> 17:33.786 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
And they say that they are going
to meet that higher standard.

17:33.786 --> 17:36.422 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
They both -- say that they
have already released more.

17:36.422 --> 17:39.058 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
They have released more health
records, they have released more
tax records than Donald

17:39.058 --> 17:41.627 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
Trump.

17:41.627 --> 17:43.896 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
They say they will release yet
more health records to prove
that this pneumonia isn't

17:43.896 --> 17:47.433 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
part of something larger.

17:47.433 --> 17:53.239 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
But there was a tweet today from
David Axelrod, the adviser to
President Obama back when he

17:53.239 --> 17:56.909 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
was running for president, that
really sums up what Susan is
talking about.

17:56.909 --> 18:00.746 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
He says: "Antibiotics can
take care of pneumonia.

18:00.746 --> 18:04.617 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
What's the cure for an unhealthy
penchant for privacy that
repeatedly creates unnecessary

18:04.617 --> 18:05.651 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
problems?"

18:05.651 --> 18:06.652 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
GWEN IFILL: OK.

18:06.652 --> 18:08.854 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
That's privacy.

18:08.854 --> 18:11.557 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Let's talk about something that
she did in full view of everyone
on Friday night.

18:11.557 --> 18:15.461 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
She gave a speech at a
fund-raiser given for her by a
gay and lesbian group.

18:15.461 --> 18:18.364 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
And she said this:

18:18.364 --> 18:25.004 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
HILLARY RODHAM CLINTON (D),
Presidential Candidate: To just
be grossly generalistic, you
could

18:25.004 --> 18:28.140 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
put half of Trump's supporters
into what I call the basket of
deplorables, right, the

18:28.140 --> 18:39.251 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
racist, sexist, homophobic,
xenophobic, Islamophobic, you
name it.

18:39.251 --> 18:45.725 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
GWEN IFILL: Now, here's the
other thing that she also said.

18:45.725 --> 18:50.463 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
She said: "But the other basket
-- and I know this because I see
friends from all over America

18:50.463 --> 18:55.368 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
here -- I see friends from
