44:26.564 --> 44:31.269 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Still, Afghanistan is taking
steps to stand on its own.

44:31.269 --> 44:35.907 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
One project on the outskirts of
Kabul is both a symbol of the
effort to rebuild the country

44:35.907 --> 44:39.076 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
and a potent reminder
of national pride.

44:39.076 --> 44:42.713 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
Special correspondent
Jennifer Glasse reports.

44:42.713 --> 44:46.617 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JENNIFER GLASSE: Mohammad Kabir
has lived in the shadow of the
Darul Aman Palace all

44:46.617 --> 44:52.924 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
his life through years of
peace and decades of war.

44:52.924 --> 44:57.628 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
King Amanullah Khan commissioned
the building of the Neoclassical
palace in the early 1920s,

44:57.628 --> 45:02.333 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
a symbol of a modern,
progressive, independent
Afghanistan.

45:02.333 --> 45:06.070 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
It took just over two years to
build and the king lived here
about as long, before he was

45:06.070 --> 45:10.875 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
driven into exile in 1929
by a popular uprising.

45:10.875 --> 45:16.147 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Kabir, who says he's about 100,
used to play with the king's
children, then tended the

45:16.147 --> 45:20.051 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
palace garden for most of his
adult life, until the mujahideen
war that followed the

45:20.051 --> 45:24.088 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
1989 Soviet retreat
drove him away.

45:24.088 --> 45:27.725 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
He returned four years ago, and
says it's a lot different than
when it stood in its

45:27.725 --> 45:30.528 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
glory.

45:30.528 --> 45:34.432 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
MOHAMMAD KABIR, Afghanistan
(through translator): Back then,
the garden was full of fruit
trees

45:34.432 --> 45:37.301 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
and covered with grass.

45:37.301 --> 45:41.906 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Families came to picnic, listen
to music, and camp overnight.

45:41.906 --> 45:45.509 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JENNIFER GLASSE: A corner of the
gardens has been partially
restored, and there are grand

45:45.509 --> 45:48.879 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
plans for it and the
rest of the palace.

45:48.879 --> 45:54.051 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
In 2010, a professor and former
World Bank official named Ashraf
Ghani wrote that Darul

45:54.051 --> 45:57.755 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
Aman was a palace of
abandoned dreams.

45:57.755 --> 46:00.891 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Now he is president, and trying
to make it the stuff of dreams
with an all-Afghan project

46:00.891 --> 46:04.495 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
to restore it.

46:04.495 --> 46:07.198 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
For three months, hundreds of
laborers have been taking down
ceilings, and carting out

46:07.198 --> 46:09.700 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
rubble to make the
building safe.

46:09.700 --> 46:15.840 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
That process could take
until the end of the year.

46:15.840 --> 46:18.476 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
Architect Zabiullah
Suleimankhail is one of the
100-strong technical team that's
mapping

46:18.476 --> 46:19.610 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
out the reconstruction.

46:19.610 --> 46:22.380 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
There's been a lot of research.

46:22.380 --> 46:25.683 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
ZABIULLAH SULEIMANKHAIL,
Architect: The bricks they have
used to build the palace had the

46:25.683 --> 46:27.451 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
mark on them.

46:27.451 --> 46:29.954 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
JENNIFER GLASSE: The mark
of the king, he says.

46:29.954 --> 46:35.159 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
He is proud that the workers
here and the funds to pay for it
are all Afghan.

46:35.159 --> 46:38.462 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
He says this project is a source
of national pride that shows
that Afghans can work on

46:38.462 --> 46:41.032 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
their own.

46:41.032 --> 46:46.804 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
ZABIULLAH SULEIMANKHAIL: When
you're looking to the palace,
you're envisioning about or

46:46.804 --> 46:54.011 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
you're thinking about the
decades of war that Afghanistan
was faced with.

46:54.011 --> 47:02.219 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And now, when you want to build
or reconstruct this building,
it's really a point to great

47:02.219 --> 47:05.289 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
and brighter future.

47:05.289 --> 47:09.093 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JENNIFER GLASSE: The building
also points to an ambitious
past, like the grand room

47:09.093 --> 47:12.496 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
built by the king to house
the new parliament.

47:12.496 --> 47:15.833 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
He wanted the Darul Aman Palace,
which means Abode of Peace, to
be the center of a new

47:15.833 --> 47:17.535 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
city.

47:17.535 --> 47:21.238 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
He was deposed before he
could make that happen.

47:21.238 --> 47:23.507 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
President Ghani is using the
rebuilding process to reflect
his own view of what Afghanistan

47:23.507 --> 47:25.943 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
should be.

47:25.943 --> 47:30.448 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
So a quarter of the technical
staff are women, like structural
engineer Sofia Roshan.

47:30.448 --> 47:33.384 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
It's her first job
out of college.

47:33.384 --> 47:37.321 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
SOFIA ROSHAN, Structural
Engineer: It's very difficult
for -- especially for girls of
Afghanistan

47:37.321 --> 47:42.626 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
to work as a structural engineer
or architectural engineer on the
big projects of Afghanistan,

47:42.626 --> 47:45.162 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
especially palace.

47:45.162 --> 47:50.935 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And so that's that's a good
opportunity for us to work with
them and show the world that,

47:50.935 --> 47:53.370 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
yes, we can do it.

47:53.370 --> 47:57.274 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JENNIFER GLASSE: They're hoping
to complete this in three to
five years at an estimated

47:57.274 --> 48:02.413 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
cost right now of around $30
million, though planners say
costs could go 10 percent higher

48:02.413 --> 48:06.751 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
or more, depending on how much
structural damage is discovered.

48:06.751 --> 48:10.254 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
This isn't the first time that
Afghans have tried to restore
this palace.

48:10.254 --> 48:14.291 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
About four years ago, the mayor
of Kabul launched a campaign and
called on Afghans to donate

48:14.291 --> 48:18.629 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
whatever they could, from as
little as 20 cents to hundreds
of dollars.

48:18.629 --> 48:22.800 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And thousands of Afghans did,
but nobody knows where that
money went.

48:22.800 --> 48:26.937 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Lack of accountability has
fueled corruption for years
here.

48:26.937 --> 48:30.374 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Transparency International rates
Afghanistan one of world's worst
corruption offenders.

48:30.374 --> 48:36.480 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
The head of Kabul's exchange
market says it is as big as
threat as the Taliban.

48:36.480 --> 48:40.951 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
MAN (through translator): Inside
the government, we have some
criminals and warlords who are

48:40.951 --> 48:44.188 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
always fighting to keep their
influence on the nation and
government.

48:44.188 --> 48:47.124 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
And they use illegal
ways to stay in power.

48:47.124 --> 48:52.163 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
They only care about their own
profits, not what benefits the
people or the government.

48:52.163 --> 48:54.999 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JENNIFER GLASSE: Afghanistan's
finance minister says the
government is aware of the
problem

48:54.999 --> 48:57.568 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
and doing what it can.

48:57.568 --> 49:02.306 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
EKLIL AHMAD HAKIMI, Minister of
Finance: I have identified at
least 20 very corrupt
individuals

49:02.306 --> 49:04.008 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
within my ministry.

49:04.008 --> 49:07.645 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
So, I just fired them.

49:07.645 --> 49:12.449 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
Unfortunately, I regret
now why I fired them.

49:12.449 --> 49:19.423 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
I should have put them in a jail
or in a detention center to
recover the stolen public money.

49:19.423 --> 49:24.161 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
But I regret, up to now, we
don't have this kind of system.

49:24.161 --> 49:30.835 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JENNIFER GLASSE: He hopes a new
anti-corruption justice center
will fill that gap.

49:30.835 --> 49:35.105 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
The Afghan government is trying
to support fruit and vegetable
sales and export.

49:35.105 --> 49:38.809 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Eighty percent of the population
is involved in agriculture, but
few make more than a subsistence

49:38.809 --> 49:42.046 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
living.

49:42.046 --> 49:45.516 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
It's the same problem about 100
miles north of the capital in
the Panjshir Valley, lots

49:45.516 --> 49:50.821 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
of promise, but not much
support realizing it.

49:50.821 --> 49:54.058 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Deep inside a hillside, these
miners are hoping to strike it
rich.

49:54.058 --> 49:56.660 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
They're looking for emeralds.

49:56.660 --> 49:59.463 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
It's a basic operation.

49:59.463 --> 50:04.001 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Pretty much everything is done
by hand, except for the blasts
that help carve out the tunnels.

50:04.001 --> 50:07.638 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
The dangers are considerable,
but so are the rewards.

50:07.638 --> 50:11.175 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
One group recently found an
emerald that sold for $80,000.

50:11.175 --> 50:16.113 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Panjshir isn't the only place in
Afghanistan with possibilities
for mining.

50:16.113 --> 50:18.916 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
There are metals, minerals and
gems all over the country that
could bring the government

50:18.916 --> 50:21.719 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
billions of dollars.

50:21.719 --> 50:24.688 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
But, in many cases, they don't
have the resources to get them
out of the ground or the
infrastructure

50:24.688 --> 50:28.626 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
to take them to market.

50:28.626 --> 50:33.330 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Last Wednesday in Western
Afghanistan, Afghan and Iranian
officials came together to
inaugurate

50:33.330 --> 50:37.368 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
a key step in building that
infrastructure, the first link
in a railway that eventually

50:37.368 --> 50:41.939 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
will connect the Iranian seaport
of Chabahar to landlocked
Afghanistan.

50:41.939 --> 50:46.577 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
This project has already
been delayed by seven years.

50:46.577 --> 50:50.948 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Afghans will be watching closely
to see whether this train line
to connect Afghanistan with

50:50.948 --> 50:54.018 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
the wider world and reduce its
dependency on exporting through
Pakistan will really

50:54.018 --> 50:59.456 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
be built.

50:59.456 --> 51:02.760 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Back at the palace, there's no
doubt that this project will be
completed.

51:02.760 --> 51:05.296 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
They say the president is
keeping close track of it.

51:05.296 --> 51:07.598 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
And they can't wait for
it to be finished.

51:07.598 --> 51:13.671 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
ZABIULLAH SULEIMANKHAIL: I'm
really just looking forward to
that day, that a day will come

51:13.671 --> 51:17.875 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
that we will face the palace,
and we will cut the ribbon, and
we will inaugurate the

51:17.875 --> 51:19.576 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
place.

51:19.576 --> 51:22.813 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
That will be the best
of my -- our life.

51:22.813 --> 51:26.717 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JENNIFER GLASSE: If that day
does come, then a new Afghan
leader will have renewed the

51:26.717 --> 51:31.689 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
dream of a king who, a century
ago, wanted to show the world a
modern independent Afghanistan.

51:31.689 --> 51:39.229 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
For the "PBS NewsHour," I'm
Jennifer Glasse in Kabul.

